                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(right)\"><placeName>Balto.</placeName>\n                <date>20 Nov 1838</date>.</p>\n            <p>My dear <addressee>Isaac</addressee></p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">Your letter to <persName>Aunt Rachael</persName> was recd<lb/> this\n                morning. Uncle is progressively improving in<lb/> health. <add>?</add> on his back\n                yet in all probability<lb/> he may set up in the next week. <sic>his</sic>\n                appetite<lb/> increases, and he indulges more freely, he will<lb/> not admit himself\n                better, he is more restive<lb/> and impatient, requiring more attention but<lb/>\n                this is the result of his improvement should<lb/> he get worse again I shall write\n                to you of<lb/> course if you dont hear from me when you<lb/> might expect it\n                attribute it to the right cause<lb/> his restoration. <persName>Aunt\n                    Rachl.</persName> eyes are as you left<lb/> them: nothing worse. <sic>the</sic>\n                rest of us in <add>?</add><lb/>\n                <add>?</add> at a loss who to growl with in your absence<lb/> and\n                        <persName><sic>Rachal</sic></persName> vinagarish<add>?</add> with best\n                regards<lb/> to all friends<lb/> Truly Yrs</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(2)\">\n                <persName role=\"author\">Dav. Judah</persName>\n            </p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3rf5m22h/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
